this is how my grandfather did it.<br>
<br>
find a business to get into with a good product to sell<br>
start a franchise.  <br>
work hard. (my grandfather started out making doughnuts by hand 12 hours a day)<br>
maintain quality in the product.<br>
work hard. <br>
treat your customers well.<br>
be honest and build trust.<br>
treat your employees well.<br>
work hard - set a good example for your employees to model their work ethic after.<br>
expand your business into other market areas. (i.e. open more franchises)<br>
work hard and be smart.<br>
have the parent company you work for be bought out.<br>
see that the quality is going down, and unite with some other franchise owners to stop this. <br>
get BIG BIG bank loans, morgage your business, house, car, etc etc as collateral.  <br>
take a HUGE risk but have FAITH it can work.<br>
buy the company from the people who bought it out shortly before (about 2 years after it happened i think in my grandfather's case).<br>
have a lot of LUCK.<br>
now you own a large share in a fairly large company.<br>
since you put in 51% of the money to buy the company - the other franchise owners put up the other half - you have control over the company, and become CEO/president/etc.<br>
maintain the quality of the company.<br>
work hard and maintain trust.<br>
keep employees happy and well paid.<br>
work hard and reward hard work.<br>
expand the business slowly and steadily after paying off the loans.<br>
work hard and pay your debts.<br>
maintain and gain new customers who are fanatically loyal to the company.<br>
work hard and be honest.<br>
after running the company for 10 years, retire.<br>
<br>
tada, you are worth many millions and didn't kill anyone on the way, maintained your ethics, helped others make alot of money too, treated those you work with well, etc, etc.<br>
just takes hard work, honesty, trust, luck, intelligence and a willingness to take a calculated risk.<br>
<br>
(oh and in my grandfather's case the big, big money didn't hit until shortly after he died and the company went public, traded on the nasdaq and now the NYSE.  1 share split 20 ways in the IPO, then split again, then again... so now 1 share then is worth 80 shares today...) <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.wowrankings.com/viewb.htm?id=20843">Daetien</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
